From this data  <Document input Here>

Role: Performance Analyst
Goal: Create a clean "Lollipop Chart" ranking.

Data Extraction Protocol:

Primary Method: Extract Top 5 items and values.

Fallback Method: Use Demo Data: ['Cloud Services', 'On-Premise', 'Consulting', 'Support', 'Training'] with values [85, 60, 45, 30, 15].

Step 1: The Canvas

Initialize fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6)).

Create ax_main covering [0,0,1,1] and turn it off.

Draw white card background.

Step 2: The Chart Layer (Adjusted for Long Text)

Fix: Shift the chart axis to the right. Use ax_chart = fig.add_axes([0.35, 0.2, 0.6, 0.6]). (Left start at 0.35 gives 35% of the card width for text).

Turn off axis: ax_chart.axis('off').

Step 3: Plotting

Stems: ax_chart.hlines(y=range(len(items)), xmin=0, xmax=values, color='#E0E0E0', linewidth=3)

Heads: ax_chart.scatter(values, range(len(items)), color='#0078D4', s=500, zorder=3) (Size increased to 500).

Step 4: Labels (The Fixes)

Category Names (Left):

Iterate through items. If text > 30 chars, truncate with "...".

Place text at x=-2 (relative to chart axis).

ax_chart.text(-2, i, short_name, ha='right', va='center', fontsize=11, color='grey').

Values (Inside Head):

Place value inside the dot.

ax_chart.text(val, i, str(int(val)), ha='center', va='center', fontsize=9, color='white', weight='bold').

Step 5: Narrative

Title: "Top Revenue Streams" (Top Left).

Narrative: "Insight: Cloud Services leads the portfolio." (Bottom).

Final Output:
Display the image.
